- https://www.xmodulo.com/secure-ssh-login-one-time-passwords-linux.html
- https://wiki.archlinux.org/title/One_Time_PassWord

```sh
sudo apt install libpam-otpw otpw-bin
```

1. In `/etc/pam.d/sshd`

    ```
	# Enable One-time password authentication
	auth       required     pam_otpw.so
	session    optional     pam_otpw.so

	# Optionally disable static password login
	#@include common-auth
	```

2. In `/etc/ssh/sshd_config`

	```
	UsePAM yes
	KbdInteractiveAuthentication yes
	```

3. `sudo service ssh restart`

4. OTPW is configured independently for each user account.

	```sh
	otpw-gen > ~/otpw_passwords
	```
